* (define :generator fibonacci (n)
  (declare (integer n))
  (let ((a 0) (b 1) (c n))
    (dotimes (i (- n 1))
      (setq c (+ a b)
            a b
            b c))
    c))
(define :input word-as-integer ()
  (let* ((word (read-line))
	(retval (parse-integer word :radix 36)))
    retval))
(define :input word-as-fibonacci ()
  "Works for small words like 'and', 'or', and 'it'."
  (let ((*print-base* 36))
    (print (fibonacci (word-as-integer)))
    (values)))
